Business Requirements Document (BRD)
Gift Voucher Redemption Feature for Product Listing

---

1. Background
- The current product listing page does not support gift voucher redemption.
- Promotional campaigns require a seamless way for users to apply gift vouchers for discounts.
- Enhancing the shopping experience will drive engagement and increase conversion rates.

2. Objective
- Enable users to redeem a gift voucher for a 25% discount on a selected product.
- Provide an intuitive interface via a dedicated button and modal popup.

3. Functional Requirements
1. Voucher Redemption Button
   - Display a "Redeem Gift Voucher" button for each product in the listing.
2. Modal Popup Interface
   - On button click, open a modal popup for voucher code entry.
   - Validate voucher code format and eligibility.
   - Show error messages for invalid or expired vouchers.
   - On successful redemption, apply a 25% discount to the selected product.
   - Update product price in real-time within the modal and on the listing.
3. User Feedback
   - Display confirmation message upon successful redemption.
   - Prevent multiple redemptions for the same product per user session.
4. Voucher Validation
   - Integrate with backend API to validate voucher codes.
   - Ensure vouchers are single-use and product-specific if required.
5. Accessibility
   - Modal and button must be accessible via keyboard navigation and screen readers.

4. Non-Functional Requirements
- Performance: Modal and price update must occur within 2 seconds.
- Security: Sanitize all user inputs; validate voucher codes server-side.
- Scalability: Support high traffic during promotional periods.
- Maintainability: Code must follow repository standards and be covered by unit/integration tests.
- Accessibility: Comply with WCAG 2.1 AA standards.

5. Acceptance Criteria
- "Redeem Gift Voucher" button is visible for all products.
- Modal popup opens and closes correctly.
- Voucher code is validated and errors are shown for invalid/expired codes.
- 25% discount is applied only for valid vouchers.
- Price updates are reflected immediately.
- User cannot redeem more than one voucher per product per session.
- All requirements are covered by automated tests.
- Accessibility checks pass for modal and button.

6. Assumptions & Constraints
- Voucher codes are provided by marketing and stored in backend.
- Only one voucher can be redeemed per product per user session.
- Feature must integrate with existing product listing and pricing logic.
- Backend API for voucher validation is available and documented.

7. Glossary (optional)
- Voucher Code: Alphanumeric code provided to users for discounts.
- Modal Popup: UI element that overlays the page for user interaction.

---

